Here's my 2 cents.

There are several problems happening:

1) Bundle with jQuery is being loaded to late - some views from `flask-admin` are trying to use it, before it actually arrives.
*Possible solution:* loading jQuery manually in `invenio/base/templates/admin_base.html`
```
{%- block _bottom_assets %}
    {{ super() }}
    <script src="{{ url_for('admin.static', filename='vendor/jquery-2.1.1.min.js') }}" type="text/javascript"></script>
{%- endblock _bottom_assets %}
```

2) ` Mismatched anonymous define() module: function (momentjs, $, exports) ...` - this happens because `datarangepicker.js` is using define (if available) to create module, but this script is called from regular src tag in `flask-admin` views rather then via RequireJS API, more on this here - http://requirejs.org/docs/errors.html#mismatch 
*Possible solution:* naming the module in  `vendor/bootstrap-daterangepicker/daterangepicker.js`
```
define("daterangepicker", ['moment', 'jquery', 'exports'], function(momentjs, $, exports) {
  root.daterangepicker = factory(root, exports, momentjs, $);
});
```

3)  `Uncaught TypeError: undefined is not a function` - it is because we are trying to call tooltip method defined in the `bootstrap.min.js` - which is at this point not available yet:
*Possible solution:* as we cannot change things in `flask-admin` and at the same time IMHO don't need this fancy tooltips, we can just mock this method in `invenio/base/templates/admin_base.html`
```
{%- block _bottom_assets %}
    {{ super() }}
    <script src="{{ url_for('admin.static', filename='vendor/jquery-2.1.1.min.js') }}" type="text/javascript"></script>
    <script>
        jQuery.fn.extend({
            tooltip: function () {
                }
        });
    </script>
    {% block tail %}{% endblock -%}
{%- endblock _bottom_assets %}
```

All of above are bigger or smaller hacks, but I hope these can give a hint for the ultimate solution :smile:

