I've managed to reproduce this issue, and rotted the bug to a missing "add_ref" call for the `Align.Process` call.
```diff
index f43c2e0d..3c032471 100644
--- a/wrappers/csharp/src/Processing.cs
+++ b/wrappers/csharp/src/Processing.cs
@@ -95,6 +95,7 @@ namespace Intel.RealSense
         public FrameSet Process(FrameSet original)
         {
             object error;
+            NativeMethods.rs2_frame_add_ref(original.m_instance.Handle, out error);
             NativeMethods.rs2_process_frame(m_instance.Handle, original.m_instance.Handle, out error);
             return queue.WaitForFrames();
         }
```
This looks like the right solution, and works fine with no leaks (or at least no frame leaks - tested manually for ~6 minutes and memory remained ~200MB, didn't perform any memory inspection).
